# 3. スタート！宮女文化祭！

Kohane: Let's see... The classroom with the copy machine should be this one.
Kohane: (We won't really know how it looks until we print it... But I have a good feeling about this design!)
Kohane: (Shiho and Minori's teams also look like they're almost done with their tasks... I'm really looking forward to seeing how everything turns out.)
Kohane: (Huh? Over there... That looks like Emu and...)
Emu: Hehe♪ Our flyer turned our super duper cute, Honami!
Honami: Hehe. Yes, it did. All that's left for us is to not make any mistakes during our performance...!
Emu: We'll be fine! So, let's do our best as the little piggies!
Kohane: (Little piggies...?)
Kohane: (Oh, that's right. Class B is putting on a play. Does that mean Emu and Honami are going to be pigs?)
Kohane: (Wait, that's Airi and Shizuku...)
Airi: Honestly, how'd you end up with the key to the chemistry lab? Didn't I tell you to go ask for the key to the home ec room...?
Shizuku: I'm sorry, Airi. I know this is going to make baking anything rather difficult, but the lab does have these Bunsen burners... Can't we use those somehow?
Airi: We're supposed to be baking, not brewing up mad concoctions...!
Mafuyu: Oh, Hinomori, Momoi, hello. What are you two doing here?
Shizuku: Hello, Asahina! The thing is, we wanted to borrow the key to the home ec room but ended up with the key to the chemistry lab...
Mafuyu: Ah, that may be because I currently have the key you're looking for. Why don't we head there together? I was thinking about hiding something there for the treasure hunt.
Airi: Really?! Thanks, Asahina! You're a lifesaver!
???: Wow! Penguins!! So many adorable penguins!
Saki: Our animal cafe's gonna look sooo cute!
Haruka: But it's going to turn into a penguin cafe at this rate if we're not careful. Did you two bring any animal-related goods that we can use?
Ichika: I bought some animal ear headbands after Saki suggested that we should. I'm a little embarrassed about wearing one, but shall we try them on together?
Kohane: (Wow... Every class is really trying their best. I guess this just means we all want the School Festival to go well...)
Kohane: Alright... I need to keep doing my best too...!
Kohane: (This is it...! B-But I feel kind of nervous.)
Minori: Morning, Kohane! This is it! The School Festival!
Kohane: Oh, Minori, Shiho! Good morning!
Minori: Let's do our best to make sure all of our guests have fun today!
Shiho: To be fair, our “guests” today are all going to be Miya Girls students since we don't open to the general public until tomorrow.
Minori: But students count as real guests!
Shiho: Yeah, I guess you're not wrong. In any case, we're gonna send shivers down their spines.
Kohane: Oh, right. You two are supposed to be wolves today.
Minori: Yup! My shift starts in the afternoon!
Minori: Let's do our best, Shiho! We gotta roar like we mean it!
Shiho: Roar? We're supposed to be wolves, not lions... But point taken. Let's do our best to really scare them.
Kohane: Hehe. Good luck.
Kohane: Oh, while we're on the subject... What are you two doing before your shifts start?
Shiho: I haven't decided... Why don't we take this opportunity to go around and take a look at what everyone's doing?
Kohane: Wait, are you sure? I thought you were going to hang out with Ichika and the others...
Shiho: Oh, we should be good for today. They all said they're gonna be busy for a while, and we aren't performing until the night festival.
Minori: Oh, really? Then, let's go see what's happening!
Kohane: Yeah!
Announcement: “The first day of the Miyamasuzaka Girls Academy School Festival will now...commence!”
Minori: Okay, we absolutely need to stop here first!!
Saki: Hello! Welcome to the Flufftacular Animal Cafe☆
Ichika: W-Welcome...!
Kohane: Oh wow..! They filled their entire classroom with animal plushies!
Saki: Wait... It's you guys! Thanks for dropping by♪
Shiho: I was wondering what your class was doing.
Shiho: Your cafe's very...cute...
Saki: Hehe. Isn't it though♪ We're gonna wait tables while wearing these animal ear headbands♪ I get to be a bunny, and Ichi gets to be a dog with droopy ears!
Minori: Wait...! Does that mean Haruka's also wearing one...?
Haruka: Oh, Minori, thanks for coming. Welcome.
Minori: Hi, Haru...
Minori: H-Haruka's wearing cat ears!!!
Minori: O-Oh no... What do I do...? A cat... On Haruka's ears... A kitty cat...
Shiho: Um, don't you mean cat ears on her...?
Haruka: Hehe. How do I look...?
Minori: Y-Y-Y-You look waaay too cute, Haruka! So cute that my head might pop off!
Ichika: Y-Your head...?
Haruka: Hehe. Thanks, Minori.
Haruka: Anyway, let me show you to your seats, and please enjoy your visit.
Haruka: Thank you for your patience. Here's your Hamster Cheek Pudding, Fluffy Bunny Tail Mousse and Soft & Squishy Doggy Cream Puff.
Kohane: Oh wow...! This is so cute! I almost wish that I didn't have to eat it...!
Shiho: ...! It's so fluffy...
Minori: And cute!
Haruka: I'm glad you like them so much. I was a little worried since I didn't have much time to practice making them.
Minori: What...?! H-Haruka, you made these?!
Haruka: Not from scratch if that's what you mean... The individual pieces of these desserts are store-bought. I just tried putting them together in a cute way.
Minori: I see... B-But I get to have a dessert that you put together, Haruka. How is this not the best cafe ever...?!
Minori: I, Minori Hanasato, promise to give a review that does this masterpiece justice!
Third Kobuta Sister: “Serves you right, Mr. Okami! Not even you can knock down the Kobuta family's superalloy house!”
Mr. Okami: “No! My precious crane... It couldn't knock down your superalloy house...”
Third Kobuta Sister: “Now, Mr. Okami, it's time for us to take you to the police!”
Eldest Kobuta Sister: “What you've done is terrible. Knocking down all those houses... You need to pay for your crimes.”
Eldest Kobuta Sister: “Willful destruction of property does come with a five-year sentence, but you'll be free once again after you've repaid your debt to society.”
Shiho: Honami's actually pretty good at acting. But this story's kind of nuts...
Kohane: I was wondering what they meant by “The Real Three Little Pigs”... Do you think someone from their class wrote the script?
Shiho: I vaguely remember hearing that Honami asked Tsukasa and the others for some tips...
Shiho: That'd explain a lot if Tsukasa was the one who came up with this. I mean, so many things feel off about this story...
Minori: *Sob*
Minori: That's so sad...! Mr. Okami was only knocking down the Kobuta sisters' houses because he didn't have a place to call home...
Shiho: But I guess it hits some people pretty hard...
Kohane: Hehe. Looks like it.
Minori: Hmmm...!
Shiho: I can't figure out the last riddle of this treasure hunt... Do you know what it's talking about, Kohane?
Kohane: Hmm... “Ye shall find the last treasure in a place that is always visible, but is not always seen.” Where is this “place” it's talking about...?
Minori: Somewhere that's always visible, but not always seen...? Hmm... Do we just need to keep looking for clues?
Shiho: I don't think we have time. I'm guessing we only have about a minute left...
Mafuyu: Time's up, treasure hunters!
Minori: What?! No! Already?!
Kohane: W-We spent all of our time just thinking...
Mafuyu: Thank you all for participating. As a consolation prize, you each receive a homemade quiz booklet. I hope you enjoy them.
Kohane: O-Oh, thank you very much!
Minori: Do you think Asahina was the one who came up with those riddles? They were really hard, but also really fun!
Shiho: Yeah, they were. But that last one's still really bugging me...
???: Oh, Shii, over here♪
Shiho: Uh oh... That voice...
Minori: Hey, Shizuku and Airi are inside that stall!
Shizuku: Welcome, you three. Out for a stroll together?
Kohane: Yes! We just tried our luck with the treasure hunt.
Airi: Hehe. Nice. Sounds like your brains had to do a little overtime.
Airi: So, how would you like to try some of Class 2-D's homemade sweets?
Minori: Woohoo! What kind of sweets do you...?
Minori: Th-These look like pot stickers! And this one looks like ramen!
Shiho: Wait, those aren't sweets... Hang on. Does this mean...?!
Airi: Correct! They're lookalike sweets!
Kohane: Yeah, I just noticed that these pot stickers are cookies...! And this ramen's...pound cake...?!
Airi: Heh heh heh. We baked these with our classmates. They look pretty good, right?
Shizuku: Airi came up with the recipes for these and even taught everyone how to bake them. It was like she was the teacher.
Airi: Alright, take your pick! We've even got some over here that look just like takoyaki.
Minori: That's so cool! Okay, I'd like... One of those pot sticker cookies!
Kohane: Oh, then... I think I'll have one of those takoyaki cream puffs.
Shizuku: And you'll have the ramen, right, Shii?
Shiho: Slow down. I mean, yeah, it looks like ramen... But it's not...
Shizuku: Oh no! Is it that you don't like these kinds of sweets very much...?
Shiho: Oh, geez... Okay, okay, I'll have one. Momoi, if you don't mind...
Airi: Hehe. Thank you for your purchase! We'll have them right out in a second!
Shiho: They were good, but it tasted so different to what it looked like... My mind was having trouble comprehending what I was eating.
Kohane: Hehe. That made eating them all the more fun!
Minori: We went to the animal cafe, saw a play, tried solving some riddles, had some sweets... And it's not even noon yet! We've done so much already!
Shiho: I hate to rain on your parade, but we still have work to do.
Minori: Oh, I almost forgot!
Minori: Alright, let's do our best to make our haunted house as cute, scary and fun as possible!
Shiho & Kohane: Yeah!
Kohane: Make sure to stop by Class 1-A! We're doing a haunted house called “Little Red Riding Hood and the Young Goats' Slightly Scary Forest Adventure”!
Kohane: You don't have to be a thrill seeker! It's meant to be fun for everyone...!
Students: So, it's a haunted house that's not too scary? Can you tell us more?
Kohane: Oh, you can choose to make it a game by becoming a hunter with a gun who can chase away the wolves...!
Kohane: Before you enter, you can choose that or enjoy it as a normal haunted house! Wh-What do you think...?
Students: Hey, that sounds fun...! Wanna check it out? I kinda want to see what it's like.
Kohane: Th-Thank you very much...! I hope you all enjoy!
Haruka: Oh, Kohane. Are you on advertising duty right now?
Kohane: Huh? Haruka! Shouldn't you be at your cafe?!
Haruka: My shift just ended, so we decided to have a look around.
Kohane: ...! Oh, you're all here! Please enjoy!
Mischievous Wolf: *Howl* I'm gonna gobble you up!
Saki: Oh no! A wolf! Wait, it's eyes are so big... That's so cute♪
Ichika: Hehe. Yes, it is. But don't forget that you're the hunter, Saki. You have to shoot any wolves you see.
Saki: Oh, I forgot! Bang! Bang!
Mischievous Wolf: *Squeal* Oof...
Haruka: Hehe. You just took out the Big Bad Minori.
Cool Wolf: *Howl*
Saki: Uh oh... This one sounds like it means business...!
Students: That was so much fun! Wanna come again tomorrow?
Students: Yeah! It wasn't that scary either! My little brother's gonna love this!
Kohane: Thank goodness...!
Minori: Kohane!
Kohane: Hi, you two! Nice work! Our guests seem to be really enjoying everything!
Shiho: Yeah, I noticed that too. I saw a lot of people going through it multiple times.
Minori: Woohoo! That means our haunted house is a huge success♪
Kohane: (This also means An and the others should be able to enjoy it when they all come to visit tomorrow...!)
Kohane: (I really hope they like what we made!)
Classmate: Oh, Minori, there you all are! We have an emergency!
Minori: Huh? What's wrong?!
Classmate: One of the girls who was scheduled to be a wolf tomorrow morning got sick and won't be able to make it...
Minori: R-Really?! That's awful! During the School Festival too. But she definitely should rest...
Shiho: Doesn't that mean someone else is gonna need to fill in for her?
Classmate: About that... We're having trouble finding a replacement because a lot of girls in our class have to do club stuff in the morning.
Minori: Hmm... What do we do...? I can't really replace her since I'm already assigned to be a wolf in the morning...
Shiho: I have to run an equipment check in the morning for the night festival, so I won't be able to help either...
Kohane: ... The morning...
Kohane: (An and the others said they'd be visiting in the afternoon. So, as long as I still get to meet up with them...)
Kohane: Um... What if I replaced her?
Minori: Wait, Kohane, are you sure?!
Kohane: Yes. I've already made plans for the afternoon, but I should be free in the morning.
Classmate: Thanks, Azusawa! You're a lifesaver!
Kohane: Hehe. You're welcome.
Kohane: (Scaring people won't be easy for me... But I want our guests to have fun and enjoy themselves.)
Kohane: (So, I'm gonna do my best as a wolf tomorrow!)
